 a time when fundamentalism is the greatest religious temptation, this volume makes the case for the necessity of resurrecting the death of God.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDeath of God theology. 4aReligion and Spirituality : American Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Christianity. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh1 aAltizer, Thomas J. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobb, John B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrockett, Clayton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHass, Andrew W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCullough, Lissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, Daniel J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, Daniel J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPinnock, Sarah K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Jeffrey W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodkey, Christopher Demuth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, John K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuether, Rosemary Radford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZbaraschuk, G. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZbaraschuk, G. Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845047640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438450476423Coveruhttps:/